    "page": "PPT_sociolinguistics_page_015",
    "order": 1
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_PPT_sociolinguistics_page_015_1",
    "text": "It has long been acknowledged that there may be differences in language usage between men and women: quite extreme in languages other than English",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.0566860666282927,
      0.2460317466389253,
      0.8895348728581415,
      0.45262096251592177
    ],
    "page": "PPT_sociolinguistics_page_015",
    "order": 2
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_PPT_sociolinguistics_page_015_2",
    "text": "Lakoff (1975) identified extensive differences not just in grammar and lexis, but in aspects of style, register, and (especially in dialogues) dynamic roles",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.05668605410543776,
      0.4651162809274968,
      0.9258720859418169,
      0.620155037842475
    ],
    "page": "PPT_sociolinguistics_page_015",
    "order": 3
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_PPT_sociolinguistics_page_015_3",
    "text": "Studies have adapted to the broader social agenda: early theories relating to power relationships between sexes (Lakoff) now giving way to view that there is a cultural difference (Tannen)",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.056686054244018354,
      0.6335978840603035,
      0.9287790732753614,
      0.8353174614091357
    ],
    "page": "PPT_sociolinguistics_page_015",
    "order": 4
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_PPT_sociolinguistics_page_015_4",
    "text": "We'll look at this issue in more detail later",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
